<br>
Is there a &quot;trick&quot; to this?  They kept stopping to cast and my HP was dropping like a stone. <p><I><B>Faman Planewalker</I></B><BR>
44 Wizard on Drinal</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufaithkills.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faithkills</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/4/01 8:50:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=57.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AE kiting specs in OOT at 44</span><hr size=1> Specs are fine, but they are tricky.<br>
<br>
It's ok to get drained a couple of times before you round them up, but you don't want them getting hp back once you start blasting, so keep them snared. Don't listen to any snare free advice with specs.<br>
<br>
MR will do you no good, those drains are unresistable. If it could be resisted I would have done so once I went from 45-49 there<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Always have lev on. If your sow drops you can still get away plus you are faster over broken ground and have better field of vision.<br>
<br>
If you don't have flux staff, drop everything and get it.<br>
<br>
If there are people hunting gargs, please pull to the gob isle, ppl rarely hunt there and it's actually easier there, tho it's slow waiting for them to follow you.<br>
<br>
It's TREMENDOUSLY boring, but quite lucrative in pp and xp.<br>
<br>
FK <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufaithkills.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faithkills</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/4/01 8:53:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=57.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AE kiting specs in OOT at 44</span><hr size=1> Oh yes, the obvious... don't get close enough for them to cast, use your staff to stay at max range. The BIG annoyance of the drain is that, as you say, it breaks them up.<br>
<br>
It will usually take two snares. Rarely one, occasionally several if they get really seperated.<br>
<br>
FK <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufaman.showPublicProfile?language=EN>faman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/4/01 11:05:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=57.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AE kiting specs in OOT at 44</span><hr size=1> I have jboots (woot, got em this weekend) and flux...I guess the answer then is to stay out of casting range while kiting so they can't lifetap me.  I'll try this.<br>
<br>
I was tapped the most while trying to round them up into a tight little bunch...kite, circle (tap, tap, tap, tap, tap, tap -- OUCH!), kite, snare, kite, CoF, CoF, CoF, so on, so forth.<br>
<br>
Thank you for your help. <p><I><B>Faman Planewalker</I></B><BR>
44 Wizard on Drinal</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufaithkills.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faithkills</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/4/01 11:48:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=57.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> yep</span><hr size=1> The opening taps rounding them up are no big deal. At 48 you can even use it to know ahead of time which ones won't give xp (34hp taps are 33 lvl specs, no xp) although it really doesn't help to know, you have to kill them all anyway.<br>
<br>
After a while I didn't even bother avoiding the taps, quicker just to suck it up while pulling them than run all over to avoid a couple hundred dmg which I'd get back in the med anyway. Also running all over increases the risk of bulldozing some poor garg hunter.<br>
<br>
It seems like too much trouble at first compared to other stuff, but believe me, it gets to be rote. I died once in 4 levels, and that was because I was in the mood to play eq after drinking all night with friends. The biggest problem is not killing lowbies. I killed two ppl in that time, but one was a person that came on the island and did not announce it, so I didn't know he was there, the other I went to PAINS to avoid, but just couldn't take my advice and stay to the east half of the island for the 60 seconds it took me to pull them off the island. He had to watch the spectacle, and got too close.. with predictable results. They killed the guy so fast it didn't even scatter the grouping.<br>
<br>
FK <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showPrevMessage?topicID=57.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showNextMessage?topicID=57.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=57.topic&index=4><img src=http://www.graffe.com/messageboard/add_reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.emailToFriend?topicID=57.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.threadControl?topicID=57.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=57.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=57.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub23.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm1">General Discussion<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm2">General Quests<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm3">Trade Forum<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm4">Rant Forum<optio